@johnwardlearchitects gallery-like home is filled with impeccable crafts and art archive as an eclectic memoir of celebrated Australian architect’s adventures from childhood to now.

A film by @cocoandmaximilian. 
Music by @elliotcfmunn. 

See the full feature on yellowtrace.com.au.

#YellowtraceResidential
#YellowtraceInAus

node.text:
@dana.tomic.hughes had the pleasure of chatting with the mega talented @philippemalouin about his practice, the importance of design mentoring, staying true to yourself and the future of design. Philippe was recently involved with mentoring the finalists of #LexusDesignAward. Find out more at @discoverlexus, and keep an eye out for the Grand Prix winner announcement on September 1st ✌🏼
#YellowtraceInterviews #YellowtracePartner #TeamYellowtrace

node.text:
Since establishing @richardsandspence in 2008, Ingrid Richards and Adrian Spence have changed the face of their home city with world-class retail, hospitality and civic architecture. Here they open up their own bangin' home in Brisbane's Bowen Hills, which flips the idea of a typical house on its head 🙌🏼 📹 by @modernister for @brickworksbp, shot by @_sirap_⁠. ⁠

#YellowtraceArchitecture #YellowtraceResidential #YellowtraceInterviews #YellowtracePartner #YellowtraceXBrickworks

node.title: Take a tour through La Scala, Richards & Spence's own Brisbane home.

✨ Michael Karakolis is the founder and director of @fibonaccistone, Australia. We thought it was only fitting we got to know the man behind the brand and took a deep dive inside his fascinating brain.

Conceptualized and curated by Dana Tomić Hughes of Yellowtrace, this campaign celebrates the emotive nature of Arflex's iconic and contemporary pieces and the works of some of Australia's most exiting artistic talents. “The concept was about exploring the complementary, yet opposing nature of these uniquely Australian subjects, with the boundary-pushing furniture designs that Arflex is internationally known for.” – Dana Tomić Hughes.

Find out more about this collaboration at https://www.yellowtrace.com.au/yellowtrace-x-arflex-art-design-collaboration-curated-by-dana-tomic-hughes/

Inspired by the beauty and metaphorical significance of the island landscape, @studiomk27 has orchestrated a delicate, rhythmic design for the new resort @patinamaldives. Set amongst the Fari Islands archipelago in North Malé Atoll, delicate architectural lines remain respectfully low, never breaching the horizon, in deference to the exuberant, encompassing blues above and below.⁠ See the rest via the 🔗 in bio 😱⁠⁠⁠
⁠⁠
⁠📸 @georg_roske⁠⁠
⁠⁠

node.text:
The @fondazionevittorianobitossi has opened in Montelupo Fiorentino, showcasing the vast industrial archive of @bitossi_ceramiche – the Florentine ceramic excellence that this year celebrates the centenary of its history – revealed to the public for the first time. The museum – designed by architect @lucacipelletti, founder of AR.CH.IT – measures 1,500 square metres encompassing the production space, and preserves the original structure of premises.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
The star of the show is Bitossi’s entire historical archive – consisting of some seven thousand pieces of ceramic; a selection of plaster models and forms; work tools; a body of photographs and paper documents – all offered as a resource by professionals and the public free of charge, as an educational and consultation tool, but also a testimony and source of inspiration. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Hit the 🔗 in bio to see more.⁠ 💙⁠⁠
⁠⁠
📸 @delfino_sl / @agnese_bedini⁠⁠
⁠⁠
⁠⁠
#YellowtraceArchitecture⁠⁠
#YellowtraceCultural⁠⁠
#YellowtraceinItaly⁠⁠

With “carte blanche”, @hauvette_madani have rejuvenated this top floor apartment in Paris, reflecting the spirit of the 1930s. Restoring the bathroom to its Art Deco glory, opulent Emperador marble is balanced with Thala marble stone flooring. A custom made oak vanity continues the apartments love affair with wood, an addition that could easily be mistaken for original joinery.⁠ Trust us, you'll want to see more via the link in bio. 🤠⁠⁠

node.text:
Making his Milan debut with a bang, Unnatural Practice showcased @marcinrusak’s most recent works together with archival and in-progress pieces that inform the studio’s ongoing research. Expertly curated by @lafedesss, this solo exhibition took place at @ordet_ during #MilanDesignWeek2021 earlier this month.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
The exhibition was an insight into the many layers of the studio’s work — an opportunity to see and understand the suspended substance of Rusak’s practice as a living catalogue of the decaying, ephemeral and preserved. In his practice, elements such as flowers, leaves and plants are observed, analysed, reconstructed and transformed into raw material to be subsequently redesigned. See more via the link in bio 🍂 🙌🏼⁠⁠
⁠⁠
📷 @dsl__studio @delfino_sl⁠⁠
⁠⁠
#YellowtraceArt⁠⁠
#YellowtraceProductDesign⁠⁠

Never the ones to do things by half measures, @hermes brings another standout display during #MilanDesignWeek2021. Taking over La Pelota in Brera with a dramatic installation designed by long-term collaborator Charlotte Macaux Perelman @studiocmp, the French luxury brand unveiled their new collections for the home. For the first time ever, an audio accompaniment connects visitors to the objects. Hit the link in bio to see more 👌🏼 ⁠⁠
